<br>
Wastin Thymme<br>
Cleric of Tinkers Pride <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvalquisssilverpalm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/26/02 1:22:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting languages....</span><hr size=1> &quot;I've tried gaining skill from across the zone in group and it just doesn't work.&quot;<br>
<br>
I've tried it and it does. <p><img src=http://kanina.freeservers.com/EQSketches/Valquisssig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 664<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/26/02 11:11:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Details, Val?</span><hr size=1> My first experience with the range limit on gsay languages was in Rivervale way back near to EQ release with a hobbit druid. A friend and I were experimenting with languages and discovered the limits of range, tell, emote, say, gsay, etc. on skill gains.  The effective range seemed to be about twice /say range -- from the fish house pier, my spam victim could learn from the bridge, but not from the Inn.  Obviously, this was a normal blue server a long time ago.  Things might be different for FV.<br>
<br>
Later, on FV, I tried it again dual-boxed. I was in Swamp of No Hope with Bjond at the FV/Swamp zone. My lizard was in the safe Cabilis zone-in area. After 10 minutes of spam without a skill up, I moved my lizard teacher to the FV zone and instantly started getting skill-ups.<br>
<br>
I've not tested it comprehensively, but I have noticed that there are differences in the way zones behave wrt. various chat modes on FV. In NFP, /auc definitely has a short range. I don't see my own /aucs from the bank when I'm on the other side of the zone. In G.Fay, one box can see the other's /auc from anywhere. This seems odd to me -- it does not make sense why programmers would add zone-specific features to a global chat feaure in some zones and not others unless it's an incidental unintended side-effect of some sort (ie. bug).<br>
<br>
As a result of my experiences, I would not recommned planning on being able to learn a language across a zone.  Trying to do so is a waste of time in an already tedious and time-consuming process. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kreelos>Kreelos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/27/02 4:21:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Details, Val?</span><hr size=1> Actually it was I (OOC Val's room-mate accidentally logged in through him not myself) that posted the cross zone training incident.<br>
<br>
The case in point was in East Karana.  My group-mate and I made the mistake of trying to attack an Evil Eye.  While I stood helplessly charmed into not moving my groupmate fled and I, now the target, fled in the opposite direction.<br>
<br>
My group-mate wound up zoning into North Karana while I managed to lose the Evil Eye and headed for Highpass.  As I made the long run over the narrow pass my group-mate returned to the zone.  Before we disbanded I realised he had zoned since our last point of language training and I quickly sent him 25 lines of Elvish which promptly increased his skill.  Now we couldn't get much further apart in the zone than that (exact opposite sides) and yet there was improvement.  I have heard of other incidents of this happening so it becomes hard to know what is the exception and what is the rule. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umerelylooking.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merelylooking</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/10/02 7:50:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Should Chat channels have Language</span><hr size=1> Just wondering how people feel about this. It seems like the efforts to learn languages are useless now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/10/02 9:17:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Chat channels have Language</span><hr size=1> Why useless? As far as I know, people haven't been setting up zone channels so the whole zone can chat (which would simulate the situation on other servers). I have seen special-purpose channels set up (market, faire, etc.) to facilitate specific things... but I still run around speaking to people normally. And /smiling and /shrugging and /waving at everyone I can't understand yet. Actions do alot of speaking louder than words when you start out only speaking one of the least-used languages on Norrath.<br>
<br>
I am darn proud of the fact that I can sort of make myself understood in Human now, and chat halfway decently in Combine. I plan to continue my language studies, and am looking forward to the day when I can actually master a language other than my own. I find the languages a huge boon to the roleplay atmosphere.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Aspiring Linguist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukreelosthehunter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kreelos the Hunter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/12/02 1:50:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Chat channels have Language</span><hr size=1> Yes, I think Chat channels should have language barriers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 230<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 5:14:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Chat channels have Language</span><hr size=1> Double post, sorry. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A> at: 4/13/02 5:42:51 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 5:15:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Chat channels have Language</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;How do you learn languages that no PCs have mastered, such as Orc and Gnoll? I know you can train in them but thats an awful lot of points to be spent to master it&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
1. There are people on this server who have dumped 100 practice points for instant master in a language.  I know someone who did that to get Faerie.<br>
<br>
2. There is a process commonly called &quot;bootstrapping,&quot; which allows two people working together to develop mastery in a language, provided at least one of them knows a few words.  The process, however, is slow, at least twice as slow as learning from someone who has already mastered the language.<br>
<br>
Some people, apparently, see this as either:<br>
<br>
a) anti-role playing, or<br>
b) an exploit<br>
<br>
I'm not one of them, personally, but I've encountered people who disapproved when I suggested bootstrapping with them.  More often, people refuse because it's so time-consuming.<br>
<br>
3. Multiple characters on this sever (well, at least three, anyway) have mastery of Faerie and Dragon.<br>
<br>
4. I don't know of anyone who has master of Orc or Gnoll.  If there is anyone who has either, please contact Brunhild.  She'll give you Dragon (or Faerie, or something) in exchange.<br>
<br>
5. I'd also be willing to bootstrap Orc or Gnoll, if anyone's interested.<br>
<br>
6. It seems clear to me that Verant never intended for the chat channels to be a way around the language barrier, so using them as such is an exploit IMHO. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 10:21:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Chat channels have Language</span><hr size=1> I'll gladly bootstrap orc and gnoll with you! Yes!<br>
<br>
Of course, you might want to wait until I get 6 more levels, so I can get you above average, but hey... at least I am enthusiastic, right?<br>
<br>
Also, if ANYONE out there has even a single point in Kobold (Elder Tier'Dal), PLEASE contact me! I have someone standing by for a bootstrap session in that, so we can insult our traditional racial enemies in their own tongue.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Grr. Bark, bark. Grr. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/14/02 10:29:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Chat channels have Language</span><hr size=1> Another rumor: Supposedly someone out there has mastery of Froglok.  I am in the process of trying to hunt that person down and convince him or her to teach me.  Right now, the language which nobody seems to have is Elder Dragon.<br>
<br>
And sorry, Elly, but I have nary a word of Kobold yet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uscottystyles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scotty Styles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 10:59:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Chat channels have Language</span><hr size=1> Possible method to master all languages:<br>
<br>
I know many people have two computers, and two accounts and they will often have a druid.  A person could, theoretically, powerlevel a character up to 20 in very little time (spending no skill points at the trainer at all) then go and instantly master a language, train their main in that language, delete the level 20 character and make another to do the same with.<br>
<br>
Slow and tedious method, but it would be an easy way to learn those less common languages (gnoll, froglok, giant, etc)<br>
<br>
Also, when zoning and learning languages, do you learn languages while you're zoning, especially with the new &quot;no chat lost while zoning&quot; ability Verant put in.<br>
<br>
Thanks much! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/Thumbnails/67125button-wolf-pawprint" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 3:16:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Chat channels have Language</span><hr size=1> The more people who show up to help out at the Twilight Bastion language faires by teaching the commonly sought languages, the more likely Kenyon and I are to teach the strange ones.  Granted, we haven't mastered ALL of them yet cause we had to leave off from practicing, but we will be as soon as we get the time.  (I don't remember right now which of the strange ones we have, and haven't mastered.)<br>
<br>
